olive oil
1 bunch spring onion
½ fresh chilli
1 packet sugar snap peas
1 bunch herbs
30 g Japanese Dressing
1 tsp rice wine vinegar
½ tsp soy sauce
1 bag slaw mix
1 packet roasted peanuts

Thinly slice the spring onion and long red chilli (if using). Trim and thinly slice the sugar snap peas lengthways. Thinly slice the herbs.

In a large bowl, combine the Japanese dressing, rice wine vinegar, soy sauce and a drizzle of olive oil.

Add the slaw mix, spring onion and sugar snap peas to the dressing and toss to combine.

Transfer the Asian sugar snap pea slaw to a serving bowl. Top with the roasted peanuts, herbs and chilli (if using).